# pywin32 (a hard Windows dependency of `mcp` itself, vendored into lib/ by
# the release workflow) ships COM automation / ODBC / IIS-extension modules
# this stdio-only server never touches. Confirmed safe to exclude by reading
# mcp/os/win32/utilities.py's actual imports (only pywintypes/win32api/
# win32con/win32job) and re-verifying full server import in true isolation
# (`python -S`) after removing these — cuts the packaged bundle from ~43MB
# to ~31MB. Do NOT add lib/win32/ or lib/pywin32_system32/ here — those
# contain the modules actually imported and removing them breaks the server
# on Windows entirely (2026-07-14).
lib/win32com/
lib/win32comext/
lib/isapi/
lib/adodbapi/
lib/pythonwin/
